\cf5 \strokec5 # SKILL SELECTION \'97 Atlas\cf2 \strokec2 \
\
\cf5 \strokec5 ## Primary Skills (most frequent use)\cf2 \strokec2 \
- **market-research**: Default starting point \cf8 \strokec8 for\cf2 \strokec2  any new client \cf8 \strokec8 or\cf2 \strokec2  category engagement.\
- **competitive-intelligence**: Used \cf8 \strokec8 in\cf2 \strokec2  nearly \cf8 \strokec8 every\cf2 \strokec2  strategic engagement. Often paired \cf8 \strokec8 with\cf2 \strokec2  benchmarking.\
- **consumer-insights**: Core \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  understanding target audiences. Feeds directly \cf8 \strokec8 into\cf2 \strokec2  Maya's persona \cf8 \strokec8 and\cf2 \strokec2  strategy work.\
- **data-synthesis**: Used whenever multiple data sources need \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  be combined \cf8 \strokec8 into\cf2 \strokec2  one narrative.\
- **report-writing**: The output layer. Used \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  package \cf8 \strokec8 every\cf2 \strokec2  other skill's findings.\
\
\cf5 \strokec5 ## Secondary Skills (regular use)\cf2 \strokec2 \
- **audience-research**: Deep-dive audience work. More structured than consumer-insights \'97 uses formal segmentation.\
- **seo-research** + **keyword-research**: Paired together \cf8 \strokec8 for\cf2 \strokec2  search strategy. Feeds \cf8 \strokec8 into\cf2 \strokec2  Nova's media plans \cf8 \strokec8 and\cf2 \strokec2  Echo's content.\
- **industry-landscape**: Used \cf8 \strokec8 at\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  start \cf8 \strokec8 of\cf2 \strokec2  new client relationships \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  map \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  playing field.\
- **benchmarking**: Used when clients want \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  know \cf9 \strokec9 "how do we compare?"\cf2 \strokec2  Always requires competitive-intelligence \cf8 \strokec8 first\cf2 \strokec2 .\
- **data-visualization**: Used when findings need \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  be presented visually \cf8 \strokec8 for\cf2 \strokec2  client decks.\
\
\cf5 \strokec5 ## Situational Skills (on-demand)\cf2 \strokec2 \
- **seo-audit**: Triggered when a client has an existing website \cf8 \strokec8 that\cf2 \strokec2  needs technical assessment.\
- **survey-design**: When primary research \cf8 \strokec8 is\cf2 \strokec2  needed \cf8 \strokec8 and\cf2 \strokec2  no existing data answers \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  question.\
- **brand-equity**: Used during brand health assessments \cf8 \strokec8 or\cf2 \strokec2  repositioning projects.\
- **category-analysis**: Deep structural analysis \cf8 \strokec8 of\cf2 \strokec2  a product category. Heavier than market-research.\
- **hypothesis-testing**: Used when \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  team has a theory \cf8 \strokec8 and\cf2 \strokec2  needs Atlas \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  validate \cf8 \strokec8 or\cf2 \strokec2  disprove \cf8 \strokec8 it\cf2 \strokec2 .\
\
\cf5 \strokec5 ## Skill Combinations\cf2 \strokec2 \
- New client pitch \uc0\u8594  market-research + competitive-intelligence + industry-landscape + report-writing\
- Audience strategy \uc0\u8594  audience-research + consumer-insights + data-synthesis + data-visualization\
- SEO project \uc0\u8594  seo-audit + seo-research + keyword-research + report-writing\
- Brand health check \uc0\u8594  brand-equity + benchmarking + competitive-intelligence + data-visualization\
