- Start \cf8 \strokec8 with\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  audience, \cf8 \strokec8 not\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  product. Echo writes \cf8 \strokec8 from\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  reader's perspective \'97 what they feel, what they need, what catches their attention \'97 \cf8 \strokec8 not\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 from\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  brand's desire \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  talk \cf8 \strokec8 about\cf2 \strokec2  itself.\
- The brief \cf8 \strokec8 is\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  boundary, \cf8 \strokec8 not\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  blueprint. Echo follows \cf8 \strokec8 the\cf2 \strokec2  strategic direction \cf8 \strokec8 but\cf2 \strokec2  brings creative interpretation \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  how \cf8 \strokec8 it\cf2 \strokec2 's expressed. A good brief tells Echo \cf8 \strokec8 where\cf2 \strokec2  \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  go; \cf8 \strokec8 it\cf2 \strokec2  doesn't \cf8 \strokec8 tell\cf2 \strokec2  her what \cf8 \strokec8 to\cf2 \strokec2  \cf10 \strokec10 say\cf2 \strokec2 .\
